Subject: Re: [T2] Cylinder stud loos

On Wed, 15 Jan 2003, Roberto Alvarado wrote:

> When I was taking the heads out, one of the cylinder #3 stud loosed
> from the crank case.
> May I just tight it back ?

IF it just screwed out and didn't bring any of the case metal with it you
can just screw it back in.  Before you do so, make sure that the nut on
the other end of the stud is freed up so that you can torque the nuts
properly.

George
